STRUCTURAL: refactor(orchestrator): extract round-lifecycle helpers (US-040)

Split `_run_rounds` body into two helpers in a new leaf module
`evolve/round_lifecycle.py`:

- `_diagnose_attempt_outcome(...)` — encapsulates the L599-L1089
  attempt-diagnosis block (review-verdict routing, zero-progress
  detection, diagnostic-prefix branches).  Returns a structured
  `_AttemptOutcome(attempt_sig, checked, unchecked, round_succeeded,
  is_review_retry, review_retry_circuit_tripped)` so the orchestrator
  caller routes follow-up work without re-implementing the logic.
- `_handle_round_success(...)` — encapsulates the L1132-L1445 post-
  round-success block (hooks, check parsing, state.json, budget
  enforcement, FILE TOO LARGE detection, memory curation, SPEC
  archival, structural-change detection, convergence + party mode +
  forever restart).  Returns `(new_run_dir, new_ui, new_start_round)`
  for the forever-restart case, `None` otherwise; calls `sys.exit()`
  for budget reached (1) / structural change (3) / convergence (0).

Both helpers lazy-import their orchestrator-resident dependencies
(`_save_subprocess_diagnostic`, `_failure_signature`,
`_check_review_verdict`, etc.) via `from evolve.orchestrator import ...`
inside their bodies — preserves `patch("evolve.orchestrator.X")`
test surfaces (US-036/US-037/US-038 lesson) and the leaf-module
invariant.  Re-export at orchestrator.py bottom keeps
`evolve.orchestrator._diagnose_attempt_outcome is
evolve.round_lifecycle._diagnose_attempt_outcome`.

